  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: Signing in continues forever, so user can't sign in after switching to the custom network with invalid url\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\n1. There should be validation of the url when user tries to save new custom network.\r\n2. On sign in step: If by any reasons network is not good enough - we can show warning after some timeout, e.g 5 minutes and propose to switch back to Ropsten, so user is not stack \r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nSpinner with \"Signing you in\" is shown forever and user can't sign in\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open Profile \r\n- Turn on development mode\r\n- Tap on Network\r\n- In Network settings screen: tap on \"+\" button in the top right corner\r\n- in RPC URL write some invalid url, e.g. \"wrong\" or valid url without http://\r\n- In Name: \"wrong network\"\r\n- Save new network settings\r\n- Switch to this network and tap on Connect\r\n- Sign in to your account\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: nightly build june 7\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n",
